In lots of paranormal and skinw*lker stories a motive is someone hearing a repetitive sound; like someone crying, saying something, or bird noises, wind blowing, even car alarm or banging/gunshots, etc. the sound playing again and again like an mp3 recording repeating on loop.

E.g. someone hears a baby crying from the bushes and goes to investigate but as he approaches he realizes the cry repeats itself exactly every time like someone is playing a sound file, then is filled with horror and runs. Or hears a "hey" from the woods repeating. "hey", "hey",.

It's not something I've encountered in real life stories so depending if it's part of native folklore might be a real phenomenon or an artifact of online creepypasta copying each other. But it fits well with the Fr. Seraphim Rose idea of demonic entities making "dumb technology".
